        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-identity",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Schema First",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 420,
        "y": -535
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 210,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Concrete Schema",
        "summary": "The first hosted schema should be:\n- `users(id, primary_email, display_name, avatar_url, status, created_at, updated_at)`\n- `auth_identities(id, user_id, provider, provider_user_id, provider_email, installation_id, provider_metadata, created_at, updated_at)`\n- `user_workspaces(id, user_id, default_save_slot, selected_provider, selected_installation_id, onboarding_state, preferences, created_at, updated_at)`\n- `repo_mappings(id, workspace_id, slot, provider, owner, repo, branch, path_prefix, visibility, installation_id, is_active, created_at, updated_at)`\n\nThat is enough to make users durable without trying to model every preference on day one.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "schema-first",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "users-implementation-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "users-implementation-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-hierarchy",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Auth Attachment",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 900,
        "y": -535
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Auth Identity",
        "summary": "Attach GitHub and future providers through `auth_identities`.\n\nThat table should link each external provider account back to one canonical `users.id`. The provider record is allowed to store installation linkage and provider metadata, but it should not replace the Twilite user record itself.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "auth-attachment",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
