        "documentHtml": "<section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;box-sizing:border-box;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,252,245,0.99), rgba(255,248,235,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(146,64,14,0.16);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(180,83,9,0.10);gap:14px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;min-width:0;\"><div style=\"font:700 11px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#b45309;\">Title</div><div style=\"font:700 28px/1.12 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;word-break:break-word;\">Users Implementation Path</div></div><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;flex-shrink:0;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(180,83,9,0.1);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.04em;\">headline</span><span style=\"font:600 10px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#9a3412;opacity:0.72;\">active</span></div></div><div style=\"height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(245,158,11,0.45), rgba(245,158,11,0));\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.65 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#4b5563;\">First hosted execution slice for Twilite users: persisted records, provider attachment, workspace resolution, and work-as-default save behavior.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Define the implementation path</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(16,185,129,0.16);color:#047857;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Task</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #10b981, #34d399);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Decide the concrete implementation path for hosted users, canonical user records, repo mappings, and default save behavior, then break that into shippable tasks across auth, persistence, migration, and UX.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Status: todo • Priority: high • Owner: Michael • Estimate: 2h</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Implement the first hosted users slice</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(219,39,119,0.14);color:#9d174d;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Summary</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #db2777, #f472b6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\"><strong>Goal:</strong> Implement the first hosted users slice<br><br><strong>Tasks In Scope</strong><br>1. Implement the hosted storage schema<br>2. Attach auth providers to the Twilite user<br>3. Resolve workspace and repo mappings on sign-in<br>4. Make work the default save destination<br><br><strong>Open Questions</strong><br>1. What remains unresolved?</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">0/4 tasks complete • 0/1 questions answered</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"users-implementation-path\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Users Implementation Path</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The abstract model is done.<br><br>This graph now defines the first concrete hosted slice in code terms: four persisted records, one sign-in resolution bundle, and one default-save rule.<br><br>First slice records:<br>- `users`<br>- `auth_identities`<br>- `user_workspaces`<br>- `repo_mappings`</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"execution-boundary\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Execution Boundary</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">This first implementation slice should only make hosted identity and workspace ownership real.<br><br>Do not fold in every local preference, cache, or editor convenience state yet.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"schema-first\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Concrete Schema</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The first hosted schema should be:<br>- `users(id, primary_email, display_name, avatar_url, status, created_at, updated_at)`<br>- `auth_identities(id, user_id, provider, provider_user_id, provider_email, installation_id, provider_metadata, created_at, updated_at)`<br>- `user_workspaces(id, user_id, default_save_slot, selected_provider, selected_installation_id, onboarding_state, preferences, created_at, updated_at)`<br>- `repo_mappings(id, workspace_id, slot, provider, owner, repo, branch, path_prefix, visibility, installation_id, is_active, created_at, updated_at)`<br><br>That is enough to make users durable without trying to model every preference on day one.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"auth-attachment\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Auth Identity</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Attach GitHub and future providers through `auth_identities`.<br><br>That table should link each external provider account back to one canonical `users.id`. The provider record is allowed to store installation linkage and provider metadata, but it should not replace the Twilite user record itself.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"workspace-resolution\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Workspace Bundle</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">On sign-in, Twilite should resolve one durable workspace bundle in this order:<br>1. `users` by canonical identity<br>2. `user_workspaces` for that user<br>3. active `repo_mappings` for `work`, `public`, and `private`<br>4. `default_save_slot`, which should initially resolve to `work`<br><br>The app should stop deriving this from scattered local state once this path exists.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"migration-boundary\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Migration Boundary</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Do not migrate everything.<br><br>Move only product-critical user state in the first pass:<br>- canonical user identity<br>- provider linkage<br>- selected installation<br>- default save slot<br>- repo mappings<br>- onboarding state that must survive devices<br><br>Leave pan/zoom, recents, caches, and session-local editor convenience state where they are for now.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"suggested-sequence\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Suggested Sequence</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">1. create `users`, `auth_identities`, `user_workspaces`, and `repo_mappings`<br>2. attach GitHub sign-in and installation linkage through `auth_identities`<br>3. resolve the workspace bundle on sign-in<br>4. make `work` the default save slot for new files<br>5. move only critical hosted user state out of browser-local storage<br>6. build settings and setup flows on top of the stable schema</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"questions-to-answer\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Questions To Answer</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">- Which hosted auth and database layer will own these four records in deployment?<br>- Should every user start with exactly one workspace, or do we need multi-workspace support immediately?<br>- What installation and repo-mapping edits belong in onboarding versus later settings?</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"expected-outcome\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Expected Outcome</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Once this slice lands, Twilite will have a real hosted user foundation: a canonical user record, attached provider identities, a durable workspace, explicit slot-to-repo mappings, and a trustworthy default-save rule that follows the user across devices.</div></div></section>",
        "summarySource": "seed",
        "updatedAt": "2026-04-04T20:03:42.636Z",
        "svg": "<svg viewBox=\"0 0 220 160\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\"><rect x=\"24\" y=\"18\" width=\"172\" height=\"124\" rx=\"18\" fill=\"#fffdfa\" stroke=\"#0f172a\" stroke-width=\"5\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"38\" width=\"82\" height=\"14\" rx=\"7\" fill=\"#0f172a\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"68\" width=\"136\" height=\"16\" rx=\"8\" fill=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke=\"#111827\" stroke-width=\"3\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"96\" width=\"120\" height=\"12\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#dbeafe\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"118\" width=\"94\" height=\"12\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#e2e8f0\"/></svg>",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "document-view",
